A vintage-style timeline illustration rendered like a 1980s technical blueprint, showing an abstract software evolution visualization. Deep navy blue background with cream and amber line drawings depicting cascading layers of interconnected nodes and databases spiraling forward through time. Each era represented by increasingly complex geometric network patterns - starting with simple hexagonal clusters on the left, transforming into intricate lattice structures on the right. Faded grid lines and subtle compass roses suggest technical precision. Warm sepia tones blend with electric blue highlights where old meets new. The composition flows diagonally from bottom-left corner (sparse, simple forms) to upper-right (dense, sophisticated meshworks), suggesting 24 years of continuous evolution. Aged paper texture overlay with slightly worn edges gives authentic retro technical documentation feel.
